Airport.Name: PORTLAND-HILLSBORO
Report.Status: The pilot under instructions improper landing flare, and the flight instructors delayed remedial action.

Airport.Name: Price Coffee Airfield
Report.Status: The pilots failure to establish a stabilize approach criteria during low-level maneuvering to the runway, which resulted in a hard landing and contact with a hay bale.

Airport.Name: Unnamed Farm Strip
Report.Status: The pilots improper landing flare, which resulted in a hard, bounced landing.

Airport.Name: Southwest Washington Regional
Report.Status: The student pilots inadequate flare resulting in a loss of airplane control during landing with gusting wind conditions.

Airport.Name: SCAPPOOSE
Report.Status: The pilots failure to extend the landing gear before landing. Contributing to the accident was the pilots failure to utilize a prelanding checklist.

Airport.Name: ROSTRAVER
Report.Status: The malfunction of the braking system fluid line, which resulted in an overrun of the runway.
The pilots improper in-flight planning and fuel management that resulted in the loss of engine power due to fuel exhaustion.

Airport.Name: Private
Report.Status: The pilots excessive use of brakes which resulted in a nose-over.

Airport.Name: BRUNSWICK GOLDEN ISLES
Report.Status: An in-flight collision with a bird.
The pilots failure to maintain clearance from the power lines during a low-level application pass.

Airport.Name: WASHINGTON MUNI
Report.Status: The pilot not maintaining sufficient altitude to clear an obstruction during the aerial application flight.

Airport.Name: Salisbury Regional Airport
Report.Status: The student pilots improper flare, which resulted in a hard landing.
The pilots failure to maintain adequate clearance from crops during an agricultural flight.

Airport.Name: LAKE HOOD
Report.Status: The pilots failure to maintain directional control during takeoff in gusting wind conditions which resulted in the wing exceeding its critical angle of attack, a loss of control and impact with the water.

Airport.Name: MONTGOMERY-GIBBS EXEC
Report.Status: The student pilots unstable approach and inadequate flare which resulted in a hard, bounced landing.

The pilots improper decision to takeoff from an unimproved airstrip with a high density altitude which degraded its climb performance and led to a collision with vegetation off the end of the airstrip.

Airport.Name: TALKEETNA
Report.Status: The pilot's failure to maintain directional control during the landing roll which resulted in a runway excursion and collision with a ditch.
The pilot improperly monitored the operating environment which resulted in a collision with a tree located in the middle of a field.
The loss of engine power due to carburetor ice.  Contributing to the accident was the pilots failure to use carburetor heat.

Airport.Name: Fairbanks International Airpor
Report.Status: The pilots failure to maintain control of the airplane during landing.

Airport.Name: MORIARTY MUNI
Report.Status: The pilots failure to maintain directional control and the flight instructor's inadequate remedial action during the landing roll, which resulted in a ground loop.

Airport.Name: Egegik Airport
Report.Status: The pilot's failure to maintain directional control during takeoff from a lake.

Airport.Name: Roosterville
Report.Status: The flight instructors improper decision to take off without adequate airspeed which resulted in degraded performance and a collision with trees.

Airport.Name: Nolte Farms Airport
Report.Status: The pilots failure to maintain airplane control during landing resulting in an impact with crop and a subsequent ground-loop. Contributing was the wet turf airstrip.

Airport.Name: BLAIRSTOWN
Report.Status: The pilots decision to cross the taxiway at an unsuitable location.
The pilots failure to maintain an appropriate descent rate for a glassy water landing, which resulted in a hard landing.

Airport.Name: SOUTH VALLEY RGNL
Report.Status: The airplanes encounter with a microburst during initial climb that resulted in a loss of altitude and subsequent collision with a tree.
The pilots decision to depart during high, gusty wind conditions which resulted sink and subsequent impact with terrain.

Airport.Name: EAGLE CREEK AIRPARK
Report.Status: The student pilots incorrect application of rudder during landing and the flight instructors delayed response to the student pilots action.

Airport.Name: NORTH LAS VEGAS
Report.Status: The pilots failure to maintain airplane control during landing in gusting wind conditions.

Airport.Name: Mountain
Report.Status: The pilots inadvertent application of the brakes during the landing roll, which resulted in a nose-over and substantial damage to the rudder and wings.
The pilots loss of control during takeoff in gusting wind conditions.

Airport.Name: Fan Creek
Report.Status: The pilots failure to maintain airplane control during taxi in gusty conditions, which resulted in a nose-over and substantial damage to the rudder and wings.

Airport.Name: South Valley Regional
Report.Status: The pilots inability to see and avoid a bird while landing in dark night conditions.

Airport.Name: ELLINGTON
Report.Status: The pilots failure to secure the magneto switch before attempting to hand rotate the engine which resulted in an inadvertent engine start, a runaway airplane, and subsequent impact with parked airplanes. Contributing to the accident was the failure to properly secure the airplane with chocks.
